Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses techniques based on matrix factorizations, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper involves iterative linear algebra programs, which are often used in scientific computing and numerical analysis, indicating that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible sub-category.
